    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The theory or doctrine that society can be organized according to a cooperative model, a system based on non-profit credit and voluntary association for the exchange of services. Mutualism originated in the the writing of Pierre-Joseph Proudhon.</Note_Text>
